  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "# Cross-Entropy Method: Pendulum Swing-Up\n\nThe **Cross-Entropy Method (CEM)** is a simple, gradient-free optimization algorithm:\n1. Sample parameter vectors from a Gaussian distribution\n2. Evaluate each by simulating the system\n3. Select the top performers (\"elites\")\n4. Update the distribution mean and std from the elites\n\nNo gradients needed — just simulation + sorting. We use `np_cvode` as the physics engine and `np_randn` for sampling.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "load(\"numerics\")$\nload(\"numerics-sundials\")$\nload(\"ax-plots\")$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 8,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## 1. Pendulum Dynamics\n\nSimple pendulum with torque input $u$:\n$$\\ddot{\\theta} = -\\frac{g}{l}\\sin\\theta - b\\dot{\\theta} + \\frac{u}{ml^2}$$\n\nGoal: swing from **hanging** ($\\theta = \\pi$) to **upright** ($\\theta = 0$).",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Pendulum parameters */\ngv : 9.81$  lp : 1.0$  mp : 1.0$  bp : 0.1$\n\n/* Max torque (saturation) */\nu_max : 5.0$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 9,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## 2. Policy and Cost Function\n\nLinear policy in features $[\\sin\\theta, \\cos\\theta, \\omega]$:\n$$u = \\text{clip}(w_1 \\sin\\theta + w_2 \\cos\\theta + w_3 \\omega,\\; -u_{\\max},\\; u_{\\max})$$\n\nThese features are smooth and periodic, unlike raw $\\theta$.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Cost function: simulate one episode, return scalar cost.\n   Lower is better. Penalizes deviation from upright + control effort. */\nsimulate_cost(w1v, w2v, w3v) := block(\n  [u_expr, rhs1, rhs2, tspan_sim, traj, th_col, om_col, cost_state, n_t],\n  /* Build closed-loop dynamics with clipped control */\n  u_expr : max(-u_max, min(u_max,\n    w1v * sin(theta) + w2v * cos(theta) + w3v * omega)),\n  rhs1 : omega,\n  rhs2 : -(gv/lp)*sin(theta) - bp*omega + u_expr/(mp*lp^2),\n  tspan_sim : np_linspace(0, 6, 300),\n  /* Start hanging down: theta = pi */\n  traj : np_cvode([rhs1, rhs2], [t, theta, omega],\n                  [float(%pi), 0.0], tspan_sim, 1e-8, 1e-8),\n  /* Cost: (1 - cos(theta))^2 + 0.1*omega^2, weighted toward final states */\n  th_col : np_slice(traj, all, 1),\n  om_col : np_slice(traj, all, 2),\n  cost_state : np_add(\n    np_pow(np_sub(1.0, np_cos(th_col)), 2),\n    np_scale(0.1, np_pow(om_col, 2))),\n  n_t : first(np_shape(traj)),\n  float(np_mean(cost_state) + 2.0 * np_ref(cost_state, n_t - 1))\n)$\n\n/* Test: cost of zero controller (no torque, hangs at pi forever) */\nprint(\"Zero-controller cost:\", simulate_cost(0.0, 0.0, 0.0))$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 10,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Zero-controller cost: 12.0"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## 3. Cross-Entropy Method\n\nSample from $\\mathcal{N}(\\mu, \\sigma^2)$, evaluate, select best, update. Uses `np_randn` for efficient batch sampling.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "np_seed(42)$\n\nn_params : 3$\nn_samples : 40$\nn_elite : 8$\nn_gens : 25$\n\n/* Initial distribution */\ncem_mu : [0.0, 0.0, 0.0]$\ncem_sigma : [5.0, 5.0, 5.0]$\n\nbest_cost_history : []$\nmean_cost_history : []$\n\nfor gen : 1 thru n_gens do block(\n  [noise, samples, costs, sorted_idx, elite_params, elite_costs,\n   new_mu, new_sigma],\n\n  /* Sample: generate [n_samples, n_params] standard normal, scale by sigma, shift by mu */\n  noise : np_randn([n_samples, n_params]),\n  samples : makelist(\n    makelist(float(cem_mu[j] + cem_sigma[j] * np_ref(noise, i, j-1)), j, 1, n_params),\n    i, 0, n_samples - 1),\n\n  /* Evaluate each candidate (the expensive part: one ODE solve per sample) */\n  costs : makelist(\n    block([s], s : samples[i],\n      errcatch(simulate_cost(s[1], s[2], s[3]))),\n    i, 1, n_samples),\n  /* Replace failed simulations with high cost */\n  costs : map(lambda([c], if c = [] then 100.0 else first(c)), costs),\n\n  /* Sort by cost, select elites */\n  sorted_idx : sort(makelist(i, i, 1, n_samples),\n    lambda([a, b], costs[a] < costs[b])),\n  elite_params : makelist(samples[sorted_idx[i]], i, 1, n_elite),\n  elite_costs : makelist(costs[sorted_idx[i]], i, 1, n_elite),\n\n  /* Update distribution from elites */\n  new_mu : makelist(\n    float(lsum(p[j], p, elite_params) / n_elite),\n    j, 1, n_params),\n  new_sigma : makelist(\n    float(max(0.3, sqrt(lsum((p[j] - new_mu[j])^2, p, elite_params) / n_elite))),\n    j, 1, n_params),\n\n  cem_mu : new_mu,\n  cem_sigma : new_sigma,\n  best_cost_history : append(best_cost_history, [first(elite_costs)]),\n  mean_cost_history : append(mean_cost_history,\n    [float(lsum(c, c, elite_costs) / n_elite)]),\n\n  if mod(gen, 5) = 0 then\n    print(\"Gen\", gen, \": best =\",\n          float(round(first(elite_costs) * 1000) / 1000),\n          \"  mu =\", map(lambda([x], float(round(x * 100) / 100)), new_mu))\n)$\n\nprint(\"Final policy: w =\",\n  map(lambda([x], float(round(x * 100) / 100)), cem_mu))$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 11,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
